        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 6 at 1:42PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 142 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Gilmer, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lassater, Warren City, Pittsburg, Cason, Daingerfield, Cookville,
Roeder, Rocky Mound, Harvard, Gilmer, Ore City, Avinger, Center
Point, White Oak, Berea, Bettie, Harleton, Union Grove, Midway, and
Lone Star.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 900 PM CDT for northeastern
Texas.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 400 PM CDT for
northeastern Texas.</instruction>
